docs.abstract: A military intelligence report found that the Syrian government is expected to resume its chemical weapons program, despite President Trump saying “mission accomplished.” Here’s how the strike unfolded.
docs.snippet: A military intelligence report found that the Syrian government is expected to resume its chemical weapons program, despite President Trump saying “mission accomplished.” Here’s how the strike unfolded.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A barrage of missiles against Syria by American, French and British forces most likely will not stop President Bashar al-Assad’s chemical weapons program, a Pentagon assessment has concluded, despite President Trump’s “Mission Accomplished!” declaration hours after last weekend’s strikes.

headline.main: Missile Strikes Are Unlikely to Stop Syria’s Chemical Attacks, Pentagon Says
headline.print_headline: Strikes Unlikely to Halt Syria’s Chemical Plans, Pentagon Report Warns

docs.abstract: As a Marine general, John F. Kelly was used to defending subordinates. Standing up for a White House aide accused of abuse has raised the specter of his own resignation.
docs.snippet: As a Marine general, John F. Kelly was used to defending subordinates. Standing up for a White House aide accused of abuse has raised the specter of his own resignation.
docs.lead_paragraph: In 2013, John F. Kelly, a general at the time, defended a junior Marine officer who was accused of poor leadership after going on patrol in Afghanistan with team members who urinated on the bodies of three dead Taliban militants. Two years later, in 2015, he stood up for a Marine colonel facing a litany of charges, including sexual harassment.

headline.main: White House Chief of Staff Is a Longtime Defender of the Accused

docs.abstract: The president’s promotion of the unconfirmed claims he calls “Spygate” continues a long history of presidential trafficking in tales of shadowy cabals and secret plots.
docs.snippet: The president’s promotion of the unconfirmed claims he calls “Spygate” continues a long history of presidential trafficking in tales of shadowy cabals and secret plots.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As a candidate, Donald J. Trump claimed that the United States government had known in advance about the Sept. 11 attacks. He hinted that Antonin Scalia, a Supreme Court justice who died in his sleep two years ago, had been murdered. And for years, Mr. Trump pushed the notion that President Barack Obama had been born in Kenya rather than Honolulu, making him ineligible for the presidency.

headline.main: With ‘Spygate,’ Trump Shows How He Uses Conspiracy Theories to Erode Trust
headline.print_headline: Trump Embraces Shadowy Plots, Eroding Trust
